This paper deals with image processing and unsupervised machine learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on locating the centers of convex objects, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of clustering algorithms for this task also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper's application to biological image analysis suggests that it could also be categorized under scientific computing (cs.SI).
